**Correct Formal Proof Sketch in Lean:**

```lean
theorem vec_set_map {α β} {v : Vector α n} {idx : Fin n} {elt : α}
    {f : (idx : ℕ) → α → (idx < n) → β} :
    (v.set (↑idx) elt).mapFinIdx f = (v.mapFinIdx f).set (↑idx) (f (↑idx) elt (by
      have h : (↑idx : ℕ) < n := by
        exact Fin.is_lt idx
      exact h)) := by
  apply Vector.eq_of_forall_get
  intro rep
  -- We need to prove that both sides have the same element at index `rep`
  -- Consider whether rep == idx (by their underlying values)
  by_cases h : rep.val = (↑idx : ℕ)
  · -- Case: rep = idx
    -- LHS: ((v.set (↑idx) elt).mapFinIdx f)[rep] = f (rep.val) ( (v.set (↑idx) elt)[rep] )
    -- But (v.set (↑idx) elt)[rep] = elt because rep.val = (↑idx : ℕ)
    -- So LHS = f (rep.val)elt _
    -- RHS: ((v.mapFinIdx f).set (↑idx) (f (↑idx) elt _))[rep] = if rep.val = (↑idx : ℕ) then f (↑idx)elt _ else _
    -- Here rep.val = (↑idx : ℕ), so RHS = f (↑idx)elt _
    -- But since rep.val = (↑idx : ℕ), f (rep.val)elt _ = f (↑idx)elt _
    simp [h, Vector.get_mapFinIdx, Vector.get_set, Fin.val_mk]
    <;>
    simp_all [Fin.ext_iff]
    <;>
    aesop
  · -- Case: rep ≠ idx
    -- LHS: ((v.set (↑idx)elt).mapFinIdx f)[rep] = f (rep.val) ( (v.set (↑idx)elt)[rep] )
    -- But (v.set (↑idx)elt)[rep] = v[rep] because rep.val ≠ (↑idx : ℕ)
    -- So LHS = f (rep.val) (v[rep]) _
    -- RHS: ((v.mapFinIdx f).set (↑idx) (f (↑idx)elt _))[rep] = if rep.val = (↑idx : ℕ) then _ else (v.mapFinIdx f)[rep]
    -- Here rep.val ≠ (↑idx : ℕ), so RHS = (v.mapFinIdx f)[rep] = f (rep.val) (v[rep]) _
    simp [h, Vector.get_mapFinIdx, Vector.get_set, Fin.val_mk]
    <;>
    simp_all [Fin.ext_iff]
    <;>
    aesop
```

